21/01/2003
TIRANA, Albania -- The regional co-operation initiative introduced by Albania, Croatia and Macedonia will speed up NATO membership and will contribute to security in the region, according to Albanian Minister of Defence Pandeli Majko and US Committee on NATO President Bruce Jackson. The two officials met Monday (20 January) in Tirana. It was Jackson's second visit in three months.
In other developments, President Alfred Moisiu met with OSCE Ambassador to Tirana Osmo Lipponen to discuss progress by the Bipartisan Commission on Electoral Reform. Lipponen commended the commission's work done and its constructive spirit. (ATA - 20/01/03)
